first_para: Jane Maria Collins (born 17 February 1962) is a Member of the European Parliament for the Yorkshire and the Humber region for the UK Independence Party. An equine physiotherapist, she formed a partnership with Katie Bloom, wife of former UKIP MEP Godfrey Bloom, in 1995, and became interested in the party.

full.extract:
Jane Maria Collins (born 17 February 1962) is a Member of the European Parliament for the Yorkshire and the Humber region for the UK Independence Party. An equine physiotherapist, she formed a partnership with Katie Bloom, wife of former UKIP MEP Godfrey Bloom, in 1995, and became interested in the party.
She was elected in 2014.
^ "UKIP Yorkshire & North Lincolnshire MEP's". UKIP Yorkshire & North Lincolnshire. Retrieved 2 November 2014.
full.title: Jane Collins
